{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d67e063f-c750-45f4-9c4d-747f5adb1979","content":"The standard approach is **`System.IO.Abstractions`** — a NuGet package that wraps all static `File`, `Directory`, `Path` calls behind an injectable `IFileSystem` interface. This avoids hand-rolling your own wrappers.\n\nHere's what the refactor looks like for your `ReportGenerator`:\n\n**1. Add the package:**\n```\ndotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions\n```\n\n**2. Inject `IFileSystem` instead of calling statics:**\n```csharp\npublic class ReportGenerator\n{\n    private readonly IFileSystem _fileSystem;\n\n    public ReportGenerator(IFileSystem fileSystem)\n    {\n        _fileSystem = fileSystem;\n    }\n\n    public string GenerateReport(string reportName)\n    {\n        // ...\n        if (!_fileSystem.Directory.Exists(outputDir))\n            _fileSystem.Directory.CreateDirectory(outputDir);\n\n        _fileSystem.File.WriteAllText(reportPath, content);\n        // ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**3. In production**, pass `new FileSystem()`. **In tests**, use `MockFileSystem` (from `System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers`):\n```csharp\nvar fs = new MockFileSystem();\nvar gen = new ReportGenerator(fs);\ngen.GenerateReport(\"sales\");\nAssert.True(fs.AllFiles.Any(f => f.Contains(\"sales\")));\n```\n\nThis gives you full in-memory file system faking with no real disk I/O in tests. Want me to apply this refactor to your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"76add8dc-f65f-4f4f-8c0c-0449ad5bbd44","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to make the static `File` and `Directory` calls testable. The best approach in .NET is to use `System.IO.Abstractions`, which provides `IFileSystem` as an injectable interface wrapping all the static `File`, `Directory`, `Path` etc. calls. This is the standard, well-established pattern.\n\nLet me provide the recommendation and, if they want, refactor the code.","outputTokens":485,"requestId":"9C43:A21C3:4931BAC:5792B0B:69F866A5"},"id":"01572474-6b8e-4823-8b03-1a4665d298cc","timestamp":"2026-05-04T09:28:15.261Z","parentId":"f27af0dd-4e5a-4722-9acf-52ac95732112"}
